ver \${\textbackslash}sigma\_\{{\textbackslash}ln Mc\}\$ and all HOD parameters. Reducing the mass threshold to \$1{\textbackslash}times 10{\textasciicircum}\{14\} {\textbackslash}; h{\textasciicircum}\{-1\} {\textbackslash}; {\textbackslash}mathrm\{M\_\{{\textbackslash}odot\}\}\$ and adding a \$z=0.15-0.35\$ redshift bin sharpens this constraint to \$0.8{\textbackslash}\%\$. The small scale \$(r\_p {$<$} 3.0 {\textbackslash}; h{\textasciicircum}\{-1\} {\textbackslash}; {\textbackslash}mathrm\{Mpc\})\$ ``mass function'' and large scale \$(r\_p {$>$} 3.0 {\textbackslash}; h{\textasciicircum}\{-1\} {\textbackslash}; {\textbackslash}mathrm\{Mpc\})\$ ``halo-mass cross-correlation'' regimes of \${\textbackslash}Delta {\textbackslash}Sigma\$ have comparable constraining power, allowing internal consistency tests from such an analysis.},
